#An example for server tcp with makefile writen in c.

* run example:
#	server - default run (port = 8888 , storage = file.txt , save = ".").

* to connect the server as a client: 
#	nc localhost "port number".
#	if port number is default use 8888.

* options:
#	server -p "port number".
#	server -t "dir/file" (directory/file.txt).
#	server -s ~/"your path".

* make install
#  Installs the executable in usr/local/bin.

* make clean
#  clear the .o files and server from the program folder.

* make uninstall
# remove the server file from usr/local/bin.